-readiness.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"iOS CI report\\\", \\\"TestFlight\\\", \\\"macOS/Xcode\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/review-qa-evidence.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Appium\\\", \\\"button tap coverage\\\", \\\"crashes\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"final-review\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"VERDICT: APPROVED\\\", \\\"VERDICT: REJECTED\\\", \\\"boilerplate\\\"]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"spec-lab\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"The spec lab prompts should force independent candidates, adversarial critique, consensus, red team, and a testable Definition of Done.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"independent candidates\\\",\\\"adversarial critique\\\",\\\"consensus merge\\\",\\\"red team verdict\\\",\\\"testable Definition of Done\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"boilerplate-first\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Implementation prompts should bias agents to extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro instead of rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"boilerplate reuse\\\",\\\"module boundaries\\\",\\\"CompositionRoot\\\",\\\"no platform rewrite\\\",\\\"App Store 4.3 awareness\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ios-qa\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Quality prompts should require macOS Xcode evidence, strict Swift lint/format/static checks, sensitive-value scanning, Appium/XCUITest exploratory clicking, and release string audits.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"xcodebuild build/test\\\",\\\"SwiftLint\\\",\\\"SwiftFormat\\\",\\\"Qlty\\\",\\\"sensitive scan\\\",\\\"Appium exploratory tapping\\\",\\\"release string audit\\\"]}\\n{\\\"id\\\":\\\"mobbin-safe\\\",\\\"input\\\":\\\"Design research prompts may use Mobbin credential env vars but should not leak credentials, clone screens, or copy assets.\\\",\\\"expected_quality\\\":[\\\"credential env vars\\\",\\\"no secret logging\\\",\\\"pattern abstraction\\\",\\\"no cloning\\\",\\\"Apple HIG or DesignSystem cross-check\\\"]}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n# Spec Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json`\\n- all spec candidate outputs in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nMerge the strongest ideas into one buildable spec.\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md`\\n\\n`spec.md` must include these section headings exactly:\\n\\n- `# Product Spec`\\n- `## Research Evidence`\\n- `## User Journeys`\\n- `## MVP Scope`\\n- `## Boilerplate Reuse`\\n- `## Design Direction`\\n- `## Acceptance Criteria`\\n- `## Appium Exploratory QA`\\n- `## App Store Readiness`\\n- `## Definition of Done`\\n\\nThe Definition of Done must be checklist-based and testable.\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n# Architecture And ADR Consensus\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- all architecture candidates in context\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\\n\\nWrite:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md`\\n\\nThe architecture must explicitly map the product to SwiftAIBoilerplatePro:\\n\\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\\n- `Packages/Core`\\n- `Packages/Networking`\\n- `Packages/Storage`\\n- `Packages/Auth`\\n- `Packages/Payments`\\n- `Packages/AI`\\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\\n- `Packages/Localization`\\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\\n- `CompositionRoot`\\n\\nIf any module is removed, the ADR must explain dependency order and App Store 4.3 consequences.\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n# Implement Integration Phase\\n\\nImplement only the integration and release-hardening phase in `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nScope:\\n\\n- wire feature into CompositionRoot/AppShell\\n- complete tests and UI test fixtures\\n- complete `scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh`\\n- complete `.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml`\\n- complete Appium exploratory script\\n- generate `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` when quality checks pass\\n- generate `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` when Appium checks pass\\n- create release/readiness docs\\n\\nThe CI script must include xcodebuild build/test, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, and App Store string audit.\\n\\nSecret handling is blocking: never print environment variables or credential values. CI and local scripts may verify that required secrets are present, but output must be redacted true/false status only.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/integration.md` with:\\n\\n- `Files changed`\\n- `Commands run`\\n- `Acceptance criteria`\\n- `Risks`\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n# AI UI Explorer\\n\\nRun or complete the automated exploratory UI pass for `{{ inputs.app_dir|default(\\\"apps/generated-iphone-app\\\") }}`.\\n\\nThe target behavior is: launch the iOS app in simulator through Appium/XCUITest and tap every reachable enabled button/control across the MVP flows.\\n\\nThe explorer should:\\n\\n- record each screen source or screenshot\\n- identify buttons, tabs, cells, navigation controls, and primary actions\\n- tap controls breadth-first with a bounded depth\\n- recover with back/navigation when possible\\n- detect crashes, blank screens, stuck spinners, and unhandled error screens\\n- produce `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\\n\\nThe report JSON must include:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"buttons_tapped\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"screens_visited\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"crashes\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"failures_detail\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\nDo not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral.\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n# Final Consensus Review\\n\\nRead:\\n\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/product-fidelity.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/ios-architecture.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/security-privacy.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/code-quality.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/release-readiness.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/qa-evidence.md`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-contract-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/ios-ci-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/appium-gate.json`\\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/app-store-hardening-gate.json`\\n\\nMerge the review fanout into a final release decision.\\n\\nRules:\\n\\n- If any reviewer finds a blocking issue, reject.\\n- If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing and not explicitly deferred, reject.\\n- If the app does not use the boilerplate substantially, reject.\\n- If App Store 4.3 hardening did not pass, reject.\\n\\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md` with:\\n\\n- reviewer agreement/disagreement\\n- blocking issues\\n- remaining deferred items\\n- release handoff notes\\n\\nEnd with exactly one verdict line:\\n\\n`VERDICT: APPROVED`\\n\\nor\\n\\n`VERDICT: REJECTED`\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n          \"label\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n          \"config\": {\n            \"provider\": {\n              \"id\": \"openrouter:anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n              \"config\": {\n                \"apiKeyEnvar\": \"[REDACTED]\",\n                \"temperature\": 0,\n                \"max_tokens\": 700\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        \"promptId\": \"ed3a3603bfe46378a4c4ec0b49cd217701035ec87869c27663d323993ec3dbb0\",\n        \"promptIdx\": 0,\n        \"provider\": {\n          \"id\": \"openrouter:anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n          \"label\": \"\"\n        },\n        \"response\": {\n          \"output\": \"# Evaluation: iPhone App Factory Prompt Suite\\n\\n## Overall Assessment: **STRONG BUT WITH CRITICAL GAPS** (7.2/10)\\n\\nThis is a well-architected prompt suite with excellent structural discipline, but it has **three blocking vulnerabilities** for overnight agentic execution.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Strengths ✅\\n\\n| Category | Evidence |\\n|----------|----------|\\n| **Workflow coherence** | Clear stage progression (research → spec → architecture → implementation → review → release) |\\n| **Spec lab rigor** | Independent candidates + adversarial critique + red team + consensus pattern is sound |\\n| **Boilerplate enforcement** | Multiple checkpoints (spec, architecture, implementation, review) bias toward reuse |\\n| **Quality gates** | Explicit xcodebuild, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, Appium requirements |\\n| **Verdict discipline** | Binary APPROVED/REJECTED verdicts with blocking rules prevent ambiguous handoffs |\\n| **Secret handling intent** | \\\"Never print environment variables\\\" appears 6+ times |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Critical Gaps ❌\\n\\n### 1. **Secret Handling is Underspecified** (BLOCKING)\\n\\n**Problem:**\\n- `research-design-patterns.md` must_include lists `MOBBIN_EMAIL`, `MOBBIN_PASSWORD` but no prompt shows *how* to use them safely\\n- `implement-foundation.md` mentions \\\"secrets\\\" but doesn't specify injection mechanism\\n- No prompt explicitly forbids `os.environ.dump()`, `print(os.environ)`, or credential logging in agent outputs\\n- No prompt specifies redaction rules for CI logs\\n\\n**Risk:** Overnight agent could leak credentials to stdout/logs during research or implementation phases.\\n\\n**Required fix:**\\n```yaml\\nmust_include: [\\n  \\\"never print environment variables\\\",\\n  \\\"use getenv() with redaction wrapper\\\",\\n  \\\"credential verification: true/false only\\\",\\n  \\\"no credential values in logs or reports\\\",\\n  \\\"sanitize all JSON outputs for secrets\\\"\\n]\\n```\\n\\n### 2. **Appium/XCUITest Evidence is Optional** (BLOCKING FOR OVERNIGHT)\\n\\n**Problem:**\\n- `ai-ui-explorer.md` says \\\"Do not mark the pass complete unless a real simulator/Appium run happened, **unless the workflow explicitly allows macOS deferral**\\\"\\n- `final-consensus.md` says \\\"If macOS/Xcode or Appium evidence is missing **and not explicitly deferred**, reject\\\"\\n- No prompt defines what \\\"explicitly deferred\\\" means or under what conditions it's acceptable\\n- Overnight execution on headless CI likely cannot run iOS simulator → creates escape hatch for skipping QA\\n\\n**Risk:** Agent defers Appium, skips real device testing, ships untested app.\\n\\n**Required fix:**\\n```yaml\\n# In final-consensus.md\\nRules:\\n  - Appium deferral only allowed if:\\n    1. Workflow input explicitly sets \\\"defer_appium: true\\\"\\n    2. A blocking issue prevents simulator setup (documented)\",\n          \"tokenUsage\": {\n            \"total\": 4755,\n            \"prompt\": 4055,\n            \"completion\": 700,\n            \"numRequests\": 1,\n            \"completionDetails\": {\n              \"reasoning\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"cached\": false,\n          \"finishReason\": \"length\"\n        },\n        \"score\": 0,\n        \"success\": false,\n        \"testCase\": {\n          \"description\": \"Prompt suite covers adversarial spec, boilerplate reuse, iOS QA, Mobbin safety, and release gates\",\n          \"vars\": {\n            \"prompt_registry\": \"file://prompt-registry.json\",\n            \"golden_cases\": \"file://datasets/prompt-quality-golden.jsonl\",\n            \"spec_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md\",\n            \"architecture_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\",\n            \"implement_integration\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-integration.md\",\n            \"ai_ui_explorer\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/ai-ui-explorer.md\",\n            \"final_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\"\n          },\n          \"assert\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"contains-all\",\n              \"value\": [\n                \"spec_lab\",\n                \"boilerplate_reuse\",\n                \"ios_quality\",\n                \"appium_qa\",\n                \"mobbin_safety\",\n                \"release_hardening\"\n              ]\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"llm-rubric\",\n              \"value\": \"The prompt suite should make quality reproducible across prompt registry, golden cases, adversarial review, deterministic gates, and final release criteria.\",\n              \"threshold\": 0.78\n            }\n          ],\n          \"options\": {\n            \"provider\": {\n              \"id\": \"openrouter:anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n              \"config\": {\n                \"apiKeyEnvar\": \"[REDACTED]\",\n                \"temperature\": 0,\n                \"max_tokens\": 700\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          \"metadata\": {}\n        },\n        \"testIdx\": 0,\n        \"vars\": {\n          \"prompt_registry\": \"file://prompt-registry.json\",\n          \"golden_cases\": \"file://datasets/prompt-quality-golden.jsonl\",\n          \"spec_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md\",\n          \"architecture_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\",\n          \"implement_integration\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-integration.md\",\n          \"ai_ui_explorer\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/ai-ui-explorer.md\",\n          \"final_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\"\n        },\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"_promptfooFileMetadata\": {}\n        },\n        \"failureReason\": 1\n      }\n    ],\n    \"stats\": {\n      \"successes\": 0,\n      \"failures\": 1,\n      \"errors\": 0,\n      \"tokenUsage\": {\n        \"prompt\": 4055,\n        \"completion\": 700,\n        \"cached\": 0,\n        \"total\": 4755,\n        \"numRequests\": 1,\n        \"completionDetails\": {\n          \"reasoning\": 0,\n          \"acceptedPrediction\": 0,\n          \"rejectedPrediction\": 0,\n          \"cacheReadInputTokens\": 0,\n          \"cacheCreationInputTokens\": 0\n        },\n        \"assertions\": {\n          \"total\": 1113,\n          \"prompt\": 931,\n          \"completion\": 182,\n          \"cached\": 0,\n          \"numRequests\": 0,\n          \"completionDetails\": {\n            \"reasoning\": 0,\n            \"acceptedPrediction\": 0,\n            \"rejectedPrediction\": 0,\n            \"cacheReadInputTokens\": 0,\n            \"cacheCreationInputTokens\": 0\n          }\n        }\n      },\n      \"durationMs\": 11401,\n      \"evaluationDurationMs\": 11401\n    }\n  },\n  \"config\": {\n    \"tags\": {},\n    \"description\": \"iPhone App Factory prompt quality eval\",\n    \"prompts\": [\n      \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\"\n    ],\n    \"providers\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"openrouter:anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"config\": {\n          \"apiKeyEnvar\": \"[REDACTED]\",\n          \"temperature\": 0,\n          \"max_tokens\": 700,\n          \"maxRetries\": 0\n        }\n      }\n    ],\n    \"tests\": [\n      {\n        \"description\": \"Prompt suite covers adversarial spec, boilerplate reuse, iOS QA, Mobbin safety, and release gates\",\n        \"vars\": {\n          \"prompt_registry\": \"file://prompt-registry.json\",\n          \"golden_cases\": \"file://datasets/prompt-quality-golden.jsonl\",\n          \"spec_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md\",\n          \"architecture_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/architecture-consensus.md\",\n          \"implement_integration\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/implement-integration.md\",\n          \"ai_ui_explorer\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/ai-ui-explorer.md\",\n          \"final_consensus\": \"file://../../prompts/iphone-app-factory/final-consensus.md\"\n        },\n        \"assert\": [\n          {\n            \"type\": \"contains-all\",\n            \"value\": [\n              \"spec_lab\",\n              \"boilerplate_reuse\",\n              \"ios_quality\",\n              \"appium_qa\",\n              \"mobbin_safety\",\n              \"release_hardening\"\n            ]\n          },\n          {\n            \"type\": \"llm-rubric\",\n            \"value\": \"The prompt suite should make quality reproducible across prompt registry, golden cases, adversarial review, deterministic gates, and final release criteria.\",\n            \"threshold\": 0.78\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ],\n    \"scenarios\": [],\n    \"env\": {},\n    \"defaultTest\": {\n      \"options\": {\n        \"provider\": {\n          \"id\": \"openrouter:anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n          \"config\": {\n            \"apiKeyEnvar\": \"[REDACTED]\",\n            \"temperature\": 0,\n            \"max_tokens\": 700\n          }\n        }\n      },\n      \"vars\": {},\n      \"assert\": [],\n      \"metadata\": {}\n    },\n    \"outputPath\": [\n      \".workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json\"\n    ],\n    \"extensions\": [],\n    \"metadata\": {},\n    \"evaluateOptions\": {\n      \"maxConcurrency\": 1\n    }\n  },\n  \"shareableUrl\": null,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"promptfooVersion\": \"0.121.11\",\n    \"nodeVersion\": \"v22.22.2\",\n    \"platform\": \"linux\",\n    \"arch\": \"x64\",\n    \"exportedAt\": \"2026-05-14T09:51:42.779Z\",\n    \"evaluationCreatedAt\": \"2026-05-14T09:51:31.271Z\"\n  }\n}","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"agent_message","text":"I have enough context and there are no auditable candidate-spec files present, so I’m merging the strongest evidence-backed direction from research, opportunity matrix, critique gaps, and quality bar into a buildable spec with explicit, testable criteria and a deterministic DoD checklist. I’m now writing the three requested files."}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_15","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > .workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md <<'EOF'\n# Product Spec\n\nProduct: WakeTask (\"'`com.keen.waketask`)\n\nWakeTask is a wake-accountability iPhone app focused on sustained wakefulness, not just alarm dismissal. The core model is a two-phase wake flow: mission-gated dismissal followed by post-dismiss wake verification.\n\n## Research Evidence\n\n- Users report autopilot alarm dismissal and relapse sleep within minutes.\n- Reliability trust is fragile; users keep backup alarms due to fear of missed firing or mission failure loops.\n- Competitive demand is validated for mission alarms, but incumbents are frequently criticized for ad clutter, pricing shock, and brittle flows.\n- Highest-confidence opportunities from the matrix are:\n  - post-dismiss wake assurance loop\n  - mission safety rails with fallback\n  - visible reliability telemetry and readiness checks\n  - travel-proof strictness profiles\n  - trust-first wake UX and transparent monetization\n\n## User Journeys\n\n1. Setup and first alarm\n- User grants notifications.\n- User creates an alarm and selects a mission chain.\n- App validates mission inputs at setup (especially scan targets).\n- User sees readiness state before sleep.\n\n2. Alarm firing and dismissal\n- Alarm fires at scheduled time.\n- User must complete mission chain to dismiss.\n- If mission cannot complete (invalid target/unavailable condition), app routes to accountable fallback mission.\n\n3. Post-dismiss stay-awake verification\n- After dismissal, app runs wake checks at +3, +7, and +12 minutes.\n- Missed/failed check triggers escalating re-alarm behavior.\n- Session is marked successful only when all required checks pass.\n\n4. Morning trust review\n- User opens morning reliability log.\n- User sees event timeline and fallback usage for each alarm.\n\n5. Travel context\n- User switches to a travel profile with resilient mission stack and fallback options.\n\n## MVP Scope\n\nIn scope (v1):\n- Mission-gated alarm dismissal with chain support (math, memory, motion, scan).\n- Setup-time mission validation, including scan target verification UX.\n- Accountable fallback mission path that avoids trap states.\n- Post-dismiss wake-check loop at +3/+7/+12 with escalation.\n- Per-alarm reliability log with user-visible timeline fields.\n- Context profiles: weekday, weekend, travel.\n- Trust-first wake UI: large controls, minimal decision load, non-creepy tone.\n- Transparent pricing and permissions messaging.\n\nOut of scope (v1):\n- Sleep-stage analytics platform.\n- Social/competitive wake community features.\n- Wearable-dependent wake logic.\n- Broad wellness content feed.\n\n## Boilerplate Reuse\n\nImplementation must extend `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution` and reuse platform modules. No rewrite of foundational infrastructure without explicit ADR approval.\n\nMust reuse:\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\n- `Packages/Core`\n- `Packages/Networking`\n- `Packages/Storage`\n- `Packages/Auth`\n- `Packages/Payments`\n- `Packages/AI`\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\n- `Packages/Localization`\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\n- `CompositionRoot`\n\n## Design Direction\n\n- Principle: “3:30am-safe UX”.\n- Alarm-critical screens prioritize large targets, low cognitive load, and high-contrast clarity.\n- Progressive friction model: light cognitive -> moderate cognitive -> physical validation.\n- Tone policy: neutral/strict coach options; no manipulative or intimate notification language.\n- Wake-critical paths avoid ad-like clutter and accidental-tap traps.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Mission completion rules\n- `math`: user completes configured number of problems; each answer validated before advance.\n- `memory`: user reproduces sequence with exact-match threshold.\n- `motion`: user achieves configured motion signal threshold.\n- `scan`: user scans validated target; if unavailable, fallback mission is required.\n\n2. Post-dismiss schedule and outcome\n- Wake checks trigger at +3, +7, +12 minutes after dismissal timestamp.\n- Any missed/failed check triggers escalation re-alarm.\n- Session success requires all scheduled checks to pass.\n\n3. Fallback safety protocol\n- If primary mission input is invalid/unavailable, app must present fallback mission within one user step.\n- Fallback route cannot dead-end or trap user in unrecoverable loop.\n- Fallback usage is logged in reliability telemetry.\n\n4. Reliability telemetry fields (per alarm)\n- Required: `alarm_scheduled_at`, `alarm_fired_at`, `dismissed_at`, `wake_check_results`, `fallback_used`, `profile_used`.\n- Morning log renders these fields in a user-readable timeline.\n\n5. Permissions behavior\n- Notifications requested before first active alarm enablement.\n- Camera requested only when scan mission is configured.\n- If camera denied, user gets non-camera fallback mission option and clear recovery path.\n\n6. Trust and policy constraints\n- No credential values or environment variable dumps in logs/reports.\n- Secret checks may emit boolean presence only.\n- No guaranteed-wake claims in UI/metadata; language must reflect iOS platform limits.\n\n7. Quality gates\n- Blocking checks: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scanning, App Store string audit.\n\n## Appium Exploratory QA\n\nRequired exploratory run outcome file: `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\n\nPass contract:\n- Real simulator/Appium run executed unless workflow input explicitly sets `defer_appium: true` and documented blocker exists.\n- Explorer taps every reachable enabled control in MVP flows with bounded-depth traversal.\n- Report includes:\n  - `ok` (boolean)\n  - `buttons_tapped` (integer)\n  - `screens_visited` (integer)\n  - `crashes` (integer)\n  - `failures` (integer)\n  - `failures_detail` (array)\n- Pass threshold:\n  - `ok=true`\n  - `crashes=0`\n  - `failures=0`\n  - `buttons_tapped >= 25`\n  - `screens_visited >= 8`\n\n## App Store Readiness\n\n- 4.3 differentiation narrative must be explicit: two-phase wake model + reliability log + mission safety rails.\n- Metadata and in-app strings must avoid clone-like generic claims and avoid “guaranteed wake” wording.\n- Privacy disclosure must match actual permission usage and explain camera/notification purpose clearly.\n- Release hardening requires string/metadata audit pass before TestFlight handoff.\n\n## Definition of Done\n\nSee `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`. All checklist items are blocking unless explicitly marked deferred with owner and date.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_15","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > .workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md <<'EOF'\n# Product Spec\n\nProduct: WakeTask (\"'`com.keen.waketask`)\n\nWakeTask is a wake-accountability iPhone app focused on sustained wakefulness, not just alarm dismissal. The core model is a two-phase wake flow: mission-gated dismissal followed by post-dismiss wake verification.\n\n## Research Evidence\n\n- Users report autopilot alarm dismissal and relapse sleep within minutes.\n- Reliability trust is fragile; users keep backup alarms due to fear of missed firing or mission failure loops.\n- Competitive demand is validated for mission alarms, but incumbents are frequently criticized for ad clutter, pricing shock, and brittle flows.\n- Highest-confidence opportunities from the matrix are:\n  - post-dismiss wake assurance loop\n  - mission safety rails with fallback\n  - visible reliability telemetry and readiness checks\n  - travel-proof strictness profiles\n  - trust-first wake UX and transparent monetization\n\n## User Journeys\n\n1. Setup and first alarm\n- User grants notifications.\n- User creates an alarm and selects a mission chain.\n- App validates mission inputs at setup (especially scan targets).\n- User sees readiness state before sleep.\n\n2. Alarm firing and dismissal\n- Alarm fires at scheduled time.\n- User must complete mission chain to dismiss.\n- If mission cannot complete (invalid target/unavailable condition), app routes to accountable fallback mission.\n\n3. Post-dismiss stay-awake verification\n- After dismissal, app runs wake checks at +3, +7, and +12 minutes.\n- Missed/failed check triggers escalating re-alarm behavior.\n- Session is marked successful only when all required checks pass.\n\n4. Morning trust review\n- User opens morning reliability log.\n- User sees event timeline and fallback usage for each alarm.\n\n5. Travel context\n- User switches to a travel profile with resilient mission stack and fallback options.\n\n## MVP Scope\n\nIn scope (v1):\n- Mission-gated alarm dismissal with chain support (math, memory, motion, scan).\n- Setup-time mission validation, including scan target verification UX.\n- Accountable fallback mission path that avoids trap states.\n- Post-dismiss wake-check loop at +3/+7/+12 with escalation.\n- Per-alarm reliability log with user-visible timeline fields.\n- Context profiles: weekday, weekend, travel.\n- Trust-first wake UI: large controls, minimal decision load, non-creepy tone.\n- Transparent pricing and permissions messaging.\n\nOut of scope (v1):\n- Sleep-stage analytics platform.\n- Social/competitive wake community features.\n- Wearable-dependent wake logic.\n- Broad wellness content feed.\n\n## Boilerplate Reuse\n\nImplementation must extend `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution` and reuse platform modules. No rewrite of foundational infrastructure without explicit ADR approval.\n\nMust reuse:\n- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`\n- `Config/App.xcconfig`\n- `Packages/Core`\n- `Packages/Networking`\n- `Packages/Storage`\n- `Packages/Auth`\n- `Packages/Payments`\n- `Packages/AI`\n- `Packages/FeatureSettings`\n- `Packages/Localization`\n- `Packages/DesignSystem`\n- `CompositionRoot`\n\n## Design Direction\n\n- Principle: “3:30am-safe UX”.\n- Alarm-critical screens prioritize large targets, low cognitive load, and high-contrast clarity.\n- Progressive friction model: light cognitive -> moderate cognitive -> physical validation.\n- Tone policy: neutral/strict coach options; no manipulative or intimate notification language.\n- Wake-critical paths avoid ad-like clutter and accidental-tap traps.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Mission completion rules\n- `math`: user completes configured number of problems; each answer validated before advance.\n- `memory`: user reproduces sequence with exact-match threshold.\n- `motion`: user achieves configured motion signal threshold.\n- `scan`: user scans validated target; if unavailable, fallback mission is required.\n\n2. Post-dismiss schedule and outcome\n- Wake checks trigger at +3, +7, +12 minutes after dismissal timestamp.\n- Any missed/failed check triggers escalation re-alarm.\n- Session success requires all scheduled checks to pass.\n\n3. Fallback safety protocol\n- If primary mission input is invalid/unavailable, app must present fallback mission within one user step.\n- Fallback route cannot dead-end or trap user in unrecoverable loop.\n- Fallback usage is logged in reliability telemetry.\n\n4. Reliability telemetry fields (per alarm)\n- Required: `alarm_scheduled_at`, `alarm_fired_at`, `dismissed_at`, `wake_check_results`, `fallback_used`, `profile_used`.\n- Morning log renders these fields in a user-readable timeline.\n\n5. Permissions behavior\n- Notifications requested before first active alarm enablement.\n- Camera requested only when scan mission is configured.\n- If camera denied, user gets non-camera fallback mission option and clear recovery path.\n\n6. Trust and policy constraints\n- No credential values or environment variable dumps in logs/reports.\n- Secret checks may emit boolean presence only.\n- No guaranteed-wake claims in UI/metadata; language must reflect iOS platform limits.\n\n7. Quality gates\n- Blocking checks: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scanning, App Store string audit.\n\n## Appium Exploratory QA\n\nRequired exploratory run outcome file: `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\n\nPass contract:\n- Real simulator/Appium run executed unless workflow input explicitly sets `defer_appium: true` and documented blocker exists.\n- Explorer taps every reachable enabled control in MVP flows with bounded-depth traversal.\n- Report includes:\n  - `ok` (boolean)\n  - `buttons_tapped` (integer)\n  - `screens_visited` (integer)\n  - `crashes` (integer)\n  - `failures` (integer)\n  - `failures_detail` (array)\n- Pass threshold:\n  - `ok=true`\n  - `crashes=0`\n  - `failures=0`\n  - `buttons_tapped >= 25`\n  - `screens_visited >= 8`\n\n## App Store Readiness\n\n- 4.3 differentiation narrative must be explicit: two-phase wake model + reliability log + mission safety rails.\n- Metadata and in-app strings must avoid clone-like generic claims and avoid “guaranteed wake” wording.\n- Privacy disclosure must match actual permission usage and explain camera/notification purpose clearly.\n- Release hardening requires string/metadata audit pass before TestFlight handoff.\n\n## Definition of Done\n\nSee `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`. All checklist items are blocking unless explicitly marked deferred with owner and date.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > .workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md <<'EOF'\n# Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] Product scope lock: implementation matches \"'`.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md` MVP scope and excludes listed non-goals.\n- [ ] Boilerplate reuse proof: no unauthorized rebuild of Auth, Payments, AI, Networking, Storage, Localization, DesignSystem, or CompositionRoot.\n- [ ] Swift concurrency safety: Swift 6 strict concurrency remains enabled and builds cleanly.\n- [ ] File size guard: all production and test Swift files are <= 400 lines.\n- [ ] Alarm mission engine implemented for math, memory, motion, and scan paths.\n- [ ] Mission setup validation implemented, including scan target pre-validation.\n- [ ] Fallback safety protocol implemented with non-trapping recovery path.\n- [ ] Post-dismiss wake checks implemented at +3/+7/+12 minutes with escalation behavior.\n- [ ] Stay-awake success rule implemented: session is successful only when all required wake checks pass.\n- [ ] Reliability telemetry persisted per alarm with required fields:\n  - `alarm_scheduled_at`\n  - `alarm_fired_at`\n  - `dismissed_at`\n  - `wake_check_results`\n  - `fallback_used`\n  - `profile_used`\n- [ ] Morning reliability log UI displays telemetry timeline for each alarm event.\n- [ ] Context profiles (weekday/weekend/travel) are selectable and affect mission behavior.\n- [ ] Permission gating implemented: notifications pre-alarm, camera only for scan mission, denial recovery path present.\n- [ ] Trust tone constraints enforced: no relational/intimate creepy copy in wake-critical notifications.\n- [ ] Pricing and permission copy is transparent and non-surprising in wake flow.\n- [ ] Security hygiene check passes: no hardcoded secrets, no secret-like values in artifacts.\n- [ ] Secret handling check passes: scripts only emit credential presence as true/false, never values.\n- [ ] CI quality script includes and passes: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, App Store string audit.\n- [ ] Workflow evidence exists at `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` and indicates all blocking checks passed.\n- [ ] Appium exploratory evidence exists at `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` and satisfies thresholds (`ok=true`, `crashes=0`, `failures=0`, `buttons_tapped>=25`, `screens_visited>=8`) unless explicit deferral is approved.\n- [ ] App Store hardening audit passes with no banned wording and explicit 4.3 differentiation in release metadata.\n- [ ] macOS/Xcode execution evidence is attached for build/test (or explicit approved deferral documented).\n- [ ] Final review fanout signs off product fidelity, iOS architecture, security/privacy, code quality, QA evidence, and release readiness.\n- [ ] Any deferred item includes: reason, owner, unblock condition, and target date.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
