{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > .workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md <<'EOF'\n# Spec Consensus\n\nDate: 2026-05-14\nApp: WakeTask (\"'`com.keen.waketask`)\n\n## Inputs reviewed\n\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/research-synthesis.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/opportunity-matrix.json`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/quality-bar.json`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/context.md`\n\nNote on candidate specs: the workspace did not contain auditable per-model candidate files (Gemini/Claude/Kimi/DeepSeek). Consensus was therefore built from the available evidence synthesis, opportunity ranking, critique gap list, and quality bar constraints.\n\n## Strongest ideas merged into final spec\n\n- Keep WakeTask positioned as a sustained wakefulness product, not a generic alarm clone.\n- Preserve the two-phase model as core differentiation:\n  - mission-gated dismissal\n  - post-dismiss wake verification (+3/+7/+12)\n- Treat mission safety rails as first-class behavior:\n  - setup-time validation\n  - accountable fallback mission\n  - no trap states\n- Make reliability visible to users via per-alarm telemetry and morning timeline log.\n- Include travel-proof strictness via context profiles (weekday/weekend/travel).\n- Bake trust into UX and release posture:\n  - low-clutter wake-critical screens\n  - transparent pricing/permissions\n  - non-creepy copy policy\n- Enforce quality bar gates as blocking and measurable, including Appium exploratory evidence and App Store 4.3 hardening.\n\n## Contradictions resolved\n\n- Strictness vs safety: strict completion is required, but fallback guarantees no unrecoverable loop.\n- Reliability promise vs iOS limits: spec avoids absolute guarantees and defines measurable telemetry outcomes.\n- Friction vs retention: progressive friction + profiles instead of universal hard mode.\n- Privacy vs camera missions: camera requested only when scan mission is chosen, with non-camera recovery path.\n- QA ambiguity: Appium deferral is only valid when explicit `defer_appium: true` and blocker documentation exist.\n\n## Testability upgrades applied\n\n- Converted vague terms (“reliable”, “strict”, “ready”) into measurable pass/fail criteria.\n- Defined required telemetry schema fields.\n- Added explicit wake-check schedule and session success rule.\n- Added numeric exploratory QA thresholds (`buttons_tapped>=25`, `screens_visited>=8`, `crashes=0`, `failures=0`).\n- Added explicit release and security checklist items in Definition of Done.\n\n## Outputs produced\n\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\n\nThese outputs satisfy required section structure, reuse constraints, and checklist-based testability requirements.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
